'''Beverly Archer''' (Born July 19, 1948) is an American actress who is perhaps best known for her television roles as [[Iola Boylen]] on ''[[Mama's Family]]''<ref name="MarshBrooks2007">{{cite book|last1=Marsh|first1=Earle F.|last2=Brooks|first2=Tim|title=The Complete Directory to Prime Time Network and Cable TV Shows, 1946-Present|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=w8KztFy6QYwC&pg=PA843|accessdate=19 November 2012|year=2007|publisher=Random House Digital, Inc.|isbn=9780345497734|page=843}}</ref> and as [[Gunnery Sergeant|Gunnery Sgt]]. Alva Bricker on ''[[Major Dad]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=wqIaAAAAIBAJ&sjid=dS0EAAAAIBAJ&pg=2712,689617&dq=beverly-archer&hl=en|title=Archer expands her range by playing a tough Marine|last=Buck|first=Jerry|date=2 January 1993|work=[[Milwaukee Journal Sentinel|The Milwaukee Journal]]|publisher=[[Associated Press|AP]]|page=T31|accessdate=19 November 2012}}</ref>

She appeared in other programs such as ''[[The Young and the Restless]]'', ''[[ALF (TV series)|ALF]]'', and the movie ''[[Project ALF]]'', along with many other guest appearances. She also wrote three ''[[ALF (TV series)|ALF]]'' episodes. She played a thieving teacher in ''[[The Brady Bunch Movie]]'', who was caught by [[Bobby Brady]]. She also appeared in two episodes of ''[[Married... with Children]]'' as Miss Hardaway, a sexually repressed librarian and abstinence counselor who is in love with [[Bud Bundy|Bud]]. In addition, she appeared in a 1994 episode of ''[[Full House]]'', where she played the role of an unsympathetic [[SAT]] test monitor. She made guest appearances on episodes of ''[[Grace Under Fire (TV series)|Grace Under Fire]]'', ''[[Family Ties]]'' and ''[[The Fall Guy]]''. She portrayed [[Nancy Walker]]'s daughter in ''[[The Nancy Walker Show]]''. Aside from acting, Archer wrote episodes for both ''Mama's Family'' and ''ALF''. She retired from acting in 2002.<ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0033639/?ref_=tt_cl_t8</ref>

