{{Infobox organization | name = Cinereach | image = Cinereach_logo_actual_size.png | image_border = | size = 100px<!-- default 200px --> | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = <!-- optional --> | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = <!-- optional --> | map2 = | abbreviation = | motto = | predecessor = | successor = | formation = 2006 <!--{{Start date and years ago|YYYY|MM|DD}}--> | type = Non-profit | status = Foundation <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = Film funding | headquarters = [[New York, NY]] | location = | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | membership = | language = <!-- official languages --> | general = <!-- Secretary General --> | leader_title = Founder & Executive Director | leader_name = Philipp Engelhorn | leader_title2 = Co-Founder | leader_name2 = Michael Raisler | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | key_people = | main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> | parent_organization = <!-- if one --> | affiliations = <!-- if any --> | budget = | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = {{URL|http://cinereach.org}} | former name = }} '''Cinereach''' is a nonprofit<ref>[https://www.irs.gov/app/pub-78/search.do?nameSearchTypeStarts=false&names=Cinereach&nameSearchTypeAll=false&city=New+York&state=NY&country=USA&deductibility=all&dispatchMethod=search&submitName=Search "Online Version of Publication 78 Search Results"]. IRS.gov.</ref> film funding organization in [[New York, NY]], founded in 2006, which provides grants, awards, an annual fellowship, and in-house film production.<ref>[http://cinereach.org Cinereach] website.</ref> The organization also has partnerships with other film development organizations such as the [[Sundance Institute]]<ref name="Smith">Smith, Shannon (July 6, 2009) [http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118005713?refcatid=2470 "Sundance adds $1.5 million grant - Cinereach to fund projects, establish fellowship"]. ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]].''</ref> and other film funding organizations.<ref>Farhat Kassab, Sally (September 6, 2011). [http://www.skollfoundation.org/skoll-foundation-extends-partnership-with-sundance-institute-documentary-film-program/ "Skoll Foundation extends partnership with Sundance Institute Documentary Film program"]. [[Skoll Foundation]].</ref>
In 2009, Cinereach funded $1.5 million of Sundance Film Festival grants over three years. The funding supports a minimum of twelve feature and documentary films developed at Sundance.<ref name="Smith"/> In June 2011, four grants each were given for post-production and development for feature films, and for documentaries, one development and two production grants were made.<ref>Means, Sean P. (June 7, 2011). [http://www.sltrib.com/sltrib/blogsmoviecricket/51960726-66/directed-film-written-grants.html.csp "Sundance Institute, Cinereach dole out money to indie film projects"]. ''[[Salt Lake Tribune]]''.</ref>
The organization provides direct annual grants to fund development, production, and post-production in documentary and feature film categories.{{citation needed|date=September 2011}}
Films supported by Cinereach in the past include: ''[[Return (2011 film)|Return]]'', ''[[Donor Unknown]]'', ''[[The Forgiveness of Blood]]'', ''[[Pariah (2011 film)|Pariah]]'', ''[[Entre&nbsp;nos]]'', ''[[Bully (2011 film)|Bully]]'', ''[[The Boy Mir]]'', ''[[Kinyarwanda (film)|Kinyarwanda]]'', and ''[[Circumstance (2011 film)|Circumstance]]''.<ref>[http://www.cinereach.org/grants/grants-recipients "Grants - Recipients"]. Cinereach.org.</ref>
Recipients of the Cinereach Producers Initiative award have included Karin Chien, Julie Goldman, Lars Knudsen, Heather Rae, Joslyn Barnes, Shrihari Sathe and Jay van Hoy.<ref>https://www.screendaily.com/news/effie-brown-among-cinereach-producer-award-recipients/5127475.article</ref>
Cinereach rebranded in 2009 with a new identity and website design by experience design firm [[Method Incorporated|Method]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jnm4R-Vkst8C&pg=PA90&lpg=PA90#v=onepage&f=false |title=LogoLounge 6: 2,000 International Identities by Leading Designers|first= Catharine |last=Fishel |first2= Bill|last2=Gardner|publisher= Rockport Publishers |year= 2011}}</ref>
