{{Infobox person | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Corinne Noel Brinkerhoff | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Lawrence, Kansas]], United States | residence = [[Los Angeles, California]] | alma_mater = {{plain list| *[[Boston University College of Communication]] *[[Truman State University]] }} | occupation = [[Television producer]], writer | years_active = 2006–present | television = ''[[The Good Wife]]'', ''[[Boston Legal]]'' }}
'''Corinne Noel Brinkerhoff''' is an American television writer and producer. She has worked on the series ''[[The Good Wife]]'' and ''[[Boston Legal]]''. She was nominated for a [[Writers Guild of America Award]] for best new series in 2010.<ref name="2010 WGA nominees">{{Cite web|url=http://www.wga.org/content/default.aspx?id=3888 |title=2010 Writers Guild Awards Television, Radio, News, Promotional Writing, and Graphic Animation Nominees Announced |accessdate=April 7, 2010 |publisher=Writers Guild of America |year=2010 |author=Gregg Mitchell, Sherry Goldman |format=Press Release |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019053744/http://www.wga.org/content/default.aspx?id=3888 |archivedate=October 19, 2013 |df= }}</ref>
==Background== Brinkerhoff was born in [[Lawrence, Kansas]], and graduated from [[Lawrence High School (Kansas)|Lawrence High School]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ljworld.com/news/2016/jun/26/lawrence-native-corinne-brinkerhoff-helms-cbs-whod/|title=Lawrence native Corinne Brinkerhoff helms CBS whodunnit 'American Gothic'|last=Hlavacek|first=Joanna|date=June 26, 2016|website=ljworld.com|accessdate=July 12, 2016}}</ref> She is an alumna of [[Truman State University]], initially majoring in [[aerospace engineering]], with a minor in creative writing.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.truman.edu/our-stories/alumni/alumna-corinne-brinkerhoff/|title=Alumna: Corinne Brinkerhoff|website=truman.edu|accessdate=July 13, 2016}}</ref> She changed majors, graduated, and took graduate studies at the [Boston University College of Communication].<ref name=Boston>{{cite web |url=http://www.bu.edu/today/2013/from-bu-to-boston-legal-and-the-good-wife/|title=From BU to ''Boston Legal'' and ''The Good Wife''|last=Ehrlich|first=Lara|date=November 5, 2013 |website=bu.edu|accessdate=July 12, 2016}}</ref>
==Career==
===''Boston Legal''=== Brinkerhoff began working in television in 2004 as the executive assistant to showrunner [[David E. Kelley]] on ''[[Boston Legal]]''. She became a writer in 2006, writing nine episodes in the entire series' run. In 2007, she became a story editor and was promoted to executive story editor in 2008.<ref name=Boston />
===''The Good Wife''=== She became a co-producer and writer for new legal drama ''[[The Good Wife]]'' in 2009, writing 10 episodes over the course of 67 episodes produced.<ref name=THR>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/american-gothic-preview-interview-corinne-905091|title='American Gothic': How 'Boston Legal,' 'Jane the Virgin' Influenced CBS' Murder Mystery Drama|last=Huggins|first=Sarah|date=June 22, 2016|website=hollywoodreporter.com|accessdate=July 12, 2016}}</ref> Brinkerhoff and the writing team were nominated for the [[Writers Guild of America Award]] for best new television series in [[Writers Guild of America Awards 2009|2010]] for their work on the first season of ''The Good Wife''.<ref name="2010 WGA nominees"/>
===''Elementary'' to present=== From 2012 to 2013, Brinkerhoff was co-executive producer for the television series ''[[Elementary (TV series)|Elementary]]'', writing three episodes and a teleplay for another. In 2014, she was co-executive producer for the short-lived series ''[[Reckless (TV series)|Reckless]]'', writing one episode. She wrote an unnamed [[Television pilot|pilot episode]] before becoming co-executive producer and writer for the television series ''[[Jane the Virgin]]'' from 2014 to 2015.<ref name=THR />
In 2016, she created the series ''[[American Gothic (2016 TV series)|American Gothic]]'', of which she is showrunner, executive producer and writer. She is also executive producer for the series ''[[No Tomorrow (TV series)|No Tomorrow]]'' that debuted in 2016.
