{{short description|Australian philosopher}} {{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Marguerite La Caze''' |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Continental philosophy|Continental]] | institutions = [[The University of Queensland]] |main_interests = [[feminist philosophy]], [[aesthetics]] | thesis_title = The analytic imaginary | thesis_url = https://espace.library.uq.edu.au/view/UQ:347000 | thesis_year = 1996 | doctoral_advisor = Michelle Boulous Walker, Tuan Nuyen | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = | alma_mater = [[The University of Queensland]] |influences = |influenced = |awards = [[Australian Research Fellow]] }}
'''Marguerite La Caze''' is an Australian philosopher and Associate Professor of [[Philosophy]] at [[the University of Queensland]]. She is an [[Australian Research Fellow]] and a former Chair of the [[Australasian Society for Continental Philosophy]] (2010-2013).<ref>{{cite web |title=History of the ASCP |url=https://www.ascp.org.au/about-the-ascp/history-of-the-ascp |website=Australasian Society for Continental Philosophy |accessdate=14 October 2018 |language=en-gb}}</ref> La Caze is known for her research on [[feminist philosophy]] and [[aesthetics]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Memon |first1=Arsalan |title=Review of Jean-Paul Sartre: Key Concepts |journal=NDPR |date=4 June 2014 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/jean-paul-sartre-key-concepts/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Fielding |first1=Helen A. |title=Review of Thinking about Love: Essays in Contemporary Continental Philosophy |journal=NDPR |date=24 March 2016 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/thinking-about-love-essays-in-contemporary-continental-philosophy/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |issn=1538-1617}}</ref>
==Books== * ''Wonder and generosity: their role in ethics and politics'', [[State University of New York Press]], 2013 * ''Integrity and the fragile self'', Ashgate, 2003 * ''The analytic imaginary'', [[Cornell University Press]], 2002
