{{Infobox NRHP | name = McPherson Opera House | nrhp_type = | image = McPherson Opera House.jpg | caption = Entrance to the McPherson Opera House | location = [[McPherson, Kansas]] | coordinates = {{coord|38|22|2|N|97|39|59|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Kansas#USA | area = | built = 1888 | architect = W.G. Reynolds; Ellison & Linn | architecture = | added = March 16, 1972 | refnum = 72001452<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2007a}}</ref> }}
'''McPherson Opera House''' is an historic [[opera]] building at 221 South Main Street in [[McPherson, Kansas]].
The house was built in 1888, opened in 1889<ref>[http://www.mcphersonoperahouse.org/then_pages/1888-1889.html 1888-1889] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120322224144/http://www.mcphersonoperahouse.org/then_pages/1888-1889.html |date=2012-03-22 }} Official site retrieved 19 April 2011]</ref><ref>[http://www.khta.com/shell.cfm?MainCat=78&SubCat=180 Kansas Historic Theatre Association] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120322224146/http://www.khta.com/shell.cfm?MainCat=78&SubCat=180 |date=2012-03-22 }} retrieved 19 April 2011</ref> and added to the National Historic Register in 1972.<ref>[http://www.kshs.org/natreg/natreg_listings/search/page:2/county:MP National and State Registers of Historic Places, McPherson County] Kansas Historical Society, retrieved 19 April 2011</ref>
